[[Image:Omer asan.jpg|right|250px|thumb|Picture of <U+00D6>mer Asan, 2005 in [[Edirne]].]]

'''<U+00D6>mer <U+015E><U+00FC>kr<U+00FC> Asan''' (born [[May 28]], [[1961]] in [[Trabzon]], [[Turkey]]), is an Turkish [[Folkloristics|folklorist]], [[Photography|photographer]] and [[writer]].

== Bibliography ==
* 1996	: ''[[Pontos K<U+00FC>lt<U+00FC>r<U+00FC>]]'' in Turkish ISBN 975-344-220-3
* 2000  : ''[[Hasan <U+0130>zzettin Dinamo]]'', biography
* 2005  : ''Niko'nun [[kemen<U+00E7>e]]si'', short stories
* Articles, stories and rasearch studies published in Radikal, Sabah and Milliyet newspapers, Gezi, Ya<U+015F>as<U+0131>n Edebiyat, Adam <U+00D6>yk<U+00FC> and Kafkasya Yaz<U+0131>lar<U+0131>, Sky Life.

== Awards obtained ==
* [[Abdi <U+0130>pek<U+00E7>i]], Peace and Friendship Award presented by Turkish-Greek Friendship Association for his article published in Milliyet newspaper.

